n1. Create a new select attribute.\n2. Add a select attribute option with value `\u003cscript\u003ealert('XSS')\u003c/script\u003e` and hit Save.\n3. Edit the newly created attribute again and see XSS dialog.\n\nThe vulnerability lays in the type_form.php file, see https://github.com/concrete5/concrete5/blob/develop/concrete/attributes/select/type_form.php#L40\n\n## Unauthenticated use\nThe vuln can be pretty bad if the website has an Express Form with select attribute associated with it that \"Allow users to add to this list.\". In that case, an (unauthenticated) user can submit a form that results to stored XSS.\n\n## Screenshot\n{F653172}\n\n## Impact\n\nStored XSS on /index.php/dashboard/pages/attributes/edit/xxx page and when editing an Express Form block.","weakness":{"id":62,"name":"Cross-site Scripting (XSS) - Stored"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":653172,"file_name":"xss-select-attribute.png","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/MbepnPh1vmynDaeVn3tt1chg?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22xss-select-attribute.png%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27xss-select-attribute.png\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fpng\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQ7LJDW226%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T090215Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECkaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJIMEYCIQCxvgGhKx%2BVpEqUvezL17KsuPm%2BUxDuHLvhZceWu%2BMLqAIhAKkG5bpt5DEPe%2F7CLdJR4L%2BDQUwTeU28cpR2l5c4MMyFKroFCPH%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2F%2FwEQAxoMMDEzNjE5Mjc0ODQ5IgwMUob3a7Wf8TICztYqjgViynfEiRCC8olGPrkLidAHWLGmj48nASMs7AmMr7Ek3A0OT%2BI6dQ0GOIUdHU3LC%2BvrGRWptjyKphafiKIEbVCEPqSzXnu%2BvBPkrscx7Ah0%2BdcvicfLr9GnC1keUBHg2GALtZT0%2BGUooCo4V8aFudk0KTSU6HaYHyocVkIrysjQfv9UJH5%2FMbUwZ0uqkbGqY2y3%2FLsQZSJ3JfcYSDLqpbsGyQ1TAmzhRdpr0%2F9lSvhlYyfINIUWi11n7gQyngl1CX%2BMiUHRPzKTTJXvY2NSWpJQWa02tUBEhQZiIL